 values of the angle between rotational-frequency and\nangular-momentum vectors to the constraints on off-diagonal components of the\nquadrupole-moment tensor. To stabilize the convergence of self-consistent\niterations, such constraints have to be taken into account. Only then one can\ndetermine the Routhian surfaces as functions of the tilting angles.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Aug 2013 19:09:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 Sep 2013 20:15:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-09-13"}
